collected in the Scottish Diabetes Survey (SDS) published by the Scottish
Diabetes Group, which combines information from many sources both in hospitals
>>>>>>> To maintain consistency with QOF, we have estimated the number of
>>>>>>> Using QOF and SDS figures with estimates from the Diabetes Prevalence
Model 2016 (Public Health England) and 2012 APHO Diabetes Prevalence Model,
there are an estimated 4.7 million people with diabetes in the UK.
>>>>>>> We estimate almost 1 million people with Type 2 diabetes don’t know
they have it because they haven’t been diagnosed.
